OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 19 Jul to Tue 28 Jul
OL,6,FRemaining predominantly dry for most
OL,7,Fparts of the country as high pressure
OL,8,Fis likely to remain close to the UK
OL,9,Ffor much of this period. However, with
OL,10,Fthe source region of the air being
OL,11,Ffrom the North Atlantic, it will be
OL,12,Fsomewhat less hot compared to many
OL,13,Frecent days. Any showers during the
OL,14,Fstart of the period are more likely
OL,15,Facross the far north. Towards the
OL,16,Flatter part of July, the influence of
OL,17,Fhigh pressure may wane somewhat,
OL,18,Fallowing a greater chance of rain,
OL,19,Fshowers or thunderstorms compared to
OL,20,Fearlier in the month. Overall,
OL,21,Ftemperatures are expected to remain
OL,22,Fabove average during this period.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
